  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Livelihood and Resilience Program</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To provide seeds to targeted households. 2) To build infrastructure that helps to increase the levels of production. 3) To support on-going animal traction activities with Farmer Groups 4) To provide technical assistance</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A sustainable improvement in the food security situation will be achieved with families in targeted communities through realizing improvements in both their livelihood and resilience capacities. During the war years the capacity of farmers to multiply and preserve sufficient quantities of quality seeds was lost due to reduced production, destruction of infrastructure, and stealing of produce by the warring factions. Since then farmers have depended on seed and tool distributions from the government and NGOs to maintain and restart their agricultural production. During the first two years of the project considerable advances were made with 6,476 participating families in the areas of agricultural training, crop diversification, seed storage structure construction, irrigation system rehabilitation, animal traction, and promotion of marketing components to assist farmers with the commercialization of their yields. The third year of the project will concentrate on strengthening capacity of smallholder farmers (3,600 families), to increase their production, marketing and commercialization of their produce through the distribution of agricultural input and training. The project will also strengthen internal Farmer Groups (FGs&#x2019;s) capacity.</narrative>
  </description>
